WEBVTT

00:04.070 --> 00:05.637
>> know what my father said
about him?

00:05.704 --> 00:07.238
>> greatest mayor ever.

00:07.306 --> 00:09.773
>> could charm a bird
out of a tree.

00:09.841 --> 00:12.578
You'll have your own plaque
some day.

00:12.646 --> 00:17.418
>> you mean, as soon as I get
over this bump in the road.

00:17.486 --> 00:20.753
>> be calm, respectful.
>> ma.

00:20.821 --> 00:22.356
Like you always say,

00:22.424 --> 00:25.225
Today's headlines wrap
tomorrow's fish.

00:26.962 --> 00:27.929
>> chris palarno.

00:27.997 --> 00:29.997
Who invited him?

00:30.065 --> 00:31.732
>> I did.

00:31.799 --> 00:32.999
Let them see we're friendly.

00:33.067 --> 00:34.568
We have nothing to hide.

00:34.636 --> 00:37.104
>> I'm your campaign manager.

00:37.172 --> 00:39.006
You should have told me.

00:41.000 --> 00:47.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:50.586 --> 00:52.953
>> mr. Palarno, did you remodel
the councilman's house

00:53.021 --> 00:54.288
In exchange
for city projects?

00:54.355 --> 00:55.722
>> councilman hayes-fitzgerald,

00:55.790 --> 00:57.724
Was mr. Palarno's work
on your home a form of a bribe?

00:57.792 --> 00:58.859
>> okay, okay.

00:58.927 --> 01:00.961
No one is hiding
from a full explanation

01:01.028 --> 01:03.430
Why a tabloid made headlines

01:03.497 --> 01:05.031
From some
of our accounting errors.

01:05.099 --> 01:07.666
>> the bribery scandal was
just the sizzle.

01:07.734 --> 01:09.701
Next comes the steak.

01:09.769 --> 01:11.269
Unless I'm made happy.

01:13.139 --> 01:15.240
50 gs by tomorrow.

01:15.307 --> 01:17.709
No way he lies his way out
of the next headline.

01:17.777 --> 01:20.846
I want my money now.

01:20.914 --> 01:23.648
>> I thought we said no more.

01:23.716 --> 01:27.385
>> we gotta bluff him,
baby.

01:27.452 --> 01:28.386
>> [shouts in spanish]
>> shh-shh.

01:28.453 --> 01:30.821
<i>Abre la puerta!</i>

01:30.889 --> 01:34.157
[pounding on door]

01:34.225 --> 01:35.425
>> you saw.

01:35.493 --> 01:36.893
I turned the heat down
with one press conference.

01:36.961 --> 01:38.694
A couple of more,
and it's gone.

01:38.762 --> 01:40.830
>> I still get
my big muni projects, though.

01:40.897 --> 01:43.699
>> we can't nurture allegations
of a quid pro quo.

01:43.766 --> 01:45.433
>> whoever hacked
into our e-mails

01:45.501 --> 01:46.868
Is stealing money
out of my pocket.

01:46.936 --> 01:48.536
I don't like it.

01:48.604 --> 01:50.604
>> chris, things will come up
in the private sector.

01:50.672 --> 01:52.072
>> tonight at the museum board's
dinner,

01:52.140 --> 01:54.407
We'll put your name in front
of all the right people.

01:54.475 --> 01:57.343
Main thing is--nothing rash.

01:57.411 --> 02:00.913
>> yeah.

02:00.981 --> 02:03.282
>> mrs. Hayes-fitzgerald, can
the kids have some ice cream?

02:03.349 --> 02:05.417
>> oh, it makes them too hyper.

02:05.485 --> 02:08.286
>> come on, josie.

02:08.354 --> 02:09.687
>> okay, I'm outnumbered.

02:09.755 --> 02:12.223
But only one scoop.

02:12.290 --> 02:13.757
If stacy calls,
tell her I'm on my cell.

02:13.825 --> 02:16.793
>> oh, goody,
we're gonna get ice cream.

02:16.861 --> 02:19.062
>> she hasn't called in days,
neil.

02:19.130 --> 02:22.232
>> I still can't believe it.

02:22.299 --> 02:25.101
>> oh, you heard the call.
Someone's bringing cash.

02:25.169 --> 02:27.436
>> I'm so glad we didn't have
to, you know,

02:27.504 --> 02:29.404
Do the other thing.

02:29.472 --> 02:33.041
>> now aruba's got
topless beaches.

02:33.109 --> 02:34.375
[chuckles]

02:37.112 --> 02:39.246
Oh, you wanna get high?

02:39.314 --> 02:41.114
Get high on this.

02:41.182 --> 02:45.084
[knock on door]

02:45.152 --> 02:47.787
Here we go.
Payday.

02:56.028 --> 02:58.997
>> [screams]

03:10.075 --> 03:13.276
[knock on door]

03:13.344 --> 03:14.911
>> stacy?

03:14.979 --> 03:18.147
Stacy, it's mom.

03:18.215 --> 03:20.216
Stacy?

03:46.507 --> 03:48.007
CC Ripped by Elderman.

04:17.430 --> 04:18.497
>> when I heard who she was,

04:18.564 --> 04:20.165
I figured
major case should be on this.

04:20.233 --> 04:22.300
>> tough week for
councilman hayes-fitzgerald.

04:22.368 --> 04:24.335
A bribery scandal
and his daughter's the victim

04:24.403 --> 04:25.736
Of a shootout.

04:25.804 --> 04:27.671
>> yeah, I'm told
she's actually his stepdaughter.

04:27.739 --> 04:30.841
>> and he is?
>> richard siebert.

04:30.909 --> 04:35.576
25. Unemployed.
Live-in boyfriend.

04:35.644 --> 04:39.612
Not the nice guy you bring home
to meet the folks.

04:39.680 --> 04:41.847
>> is this her place? His?

04:41.915 --> 04:43.615
>> her parents pay the rent.

04:43.683 --> 04:46.116
>> did she talk to anybody
before they took her

04:46.184 --> 04:47.484
To bellevue?

04:47.552 --> 04:49.619
>> uh, when I got here, she was
already in the ambulance.

04:49.686 --> 04:53.221
>> you should take that computer
in for a complete download.

04:53.289 --> 04:56.856
Looks like there's interest
in her stepdad's problems.

05:01.013 --> 05:02.013
From the notes on these margins,

05:02.081 --> 05:05.583
It looks
like she enjoyed them.

05:05.651 --> 05:07.985
>> I just spoke
with the e.R.

05:08.053 --> 05:10.087
A bullet was removed
from the girl's left shoulder.

05:10.155 --> 05:11.288
It's the same bullet
that went through him,

05:11.356 --> 05:13.456
So it's pretty deformed.

05:13.524 --> 05:14.590
She'll be okay.

05:14.658 --> 05:16.592
So the deadbolt is not broken,

05:16.660 --> 05:18.127
But the jam is splintered.

05:18.194 --> 05:20.362
Detective, you're him.

05:20.430 --> 05:21.930
So he comes to the door,

05:21.997 --> 05:23.731
He unlocks the bolt,

05:23.799 --> 05:27.101
The killer hears that,
and he kicks the door in.

05:27.169 --> 05:28.369
You jump back.

05:28.436 --> 05:30.537
Grabs the lamp.

05:30.605 --> 05:32.338
Throws it.

05:33.176 --> 05:35.377
>> and stacy's on the couch.
She jumps up.

05:35.445 --> 05:38.747
>> he turns to protect her.

05:38.815 --> 05:41.382
The killer fires again.

05:41.450 --> 05:43.384
The bullet passes through him,
hits her.

05:43.452 --> 05:45.920
He hits the ground,
bleeds out.

05:45.987 --> 05:47.654
Why was he moved?

05:47.722 --> 05:50.390
>> the mother found stacy pinned
under him.

05:50.458 --> 05:52.292
>> under his dead body?
For how long?

05:52.359 --> 05:54.961
>> from the lividity
three or four hours.

05:55.028 --> 05:56.562
Maybe she saved herself
by playing dead.

05:56.630 --> 05:59.264
>> or the killer
only wanted him.

05:59.332 --> 06:03.434
We'll do a vehicle canvass
in the area.

06:03.502 --> 06:05.269
>> you want me
to be in pain.

06:05.337 --> 06:07.504
>> you heard what she said.
No more pain medication.

06:07.572 --> 06:10.340
>> you want me
to be punished.

06:10.408 --> 06:14.643
>> stacy, this is withdrawal
that you're experiencing,

06:15.371 --> 06:17.405
I don't mean to be so blunt,

06:17.473 --> 06:19.007
But we need you to remember
what happened

06:19.074 --> 06:20.474
When it's fresh in your mind,
okay?

06:20.542 --> 06:23.677
>> I don't remember anything.

06:23.745 --> 06:24.677
I left.

06:24.745 --> 06:26.679
>> you mean you tried to escape?

06:26.747 --> 06:28.814
>> no.

06:30.984 --> 06:32.117
>> we need to know
what happened.

06:32.185 --> 06:37.420
>> after I was shot,
I could feel him

06:37.488 --> 06:40.923
In the room with me,
so I had to go.

06:40.991 --> 06:43.357
I went away.

06:43.425 --> 06:48.561
Like I was watching,
but I wasn't.

06:51.764 --> 06:55.199
But I am in pain now.

06:55.267 --> 07:00.137
Real pain.

07:00.205 --> 07:01.504
>> so councilman
hayes-fitzgerald's daughter

07:01.572 --> 07:04.775
Was shot in what appears
to be a drug crime.

07:04.842 --> 07:06.610
>> it's actually stepdaughter.

07:06.678 --> 07:09.080
Her mother was widowed.
>> whatever.

07:09.147 --> 07:10.449
My hope is a quick resolution

07:10.516 --> 07:12.617
That doesn't antagonize
a powerful politician

07:12.685 --> 07:15.786
Over an errant family member.

07:15.854 --> 07:17.621
Chief of ds is coming by.

07:17.689 --> 07:19.456
>> so far it has the look

07:19.524 --> 07:21.057
Of a drug deal gone bad.

07:21.125 --> 07:23.025
They were packed
for a flight to aruba,

07:23.093 --> 07:24.726
New clothes,
new luggage.

07:24.794 --> 07:29.730
Rick siebert might have stiffed
the wrong dealer.

07:29.798 --> 07:31.264
>> I'll tell them
a full canvass

07:31.332 --> 07:34.801
Is checking into
who that might be.

07:34.868 --> 07:38.304
>> start a canvass and suddenly
every douche bag's got a story.

07:38.372 --> 07:39.872
>> the story on you
from the landlord

07:39.939 --> 07:41.806
Is that you were banging
on rick siebert's door,

07:41.874 --> 07:43.708
Screaming threats.

07:43.776 --> 07:45.443
>> was that for drugs or money
or both?

07:45.511 --> 07:47.378
>> I got nothing to say.

07:47.446 --> 07:48.412
>> really, you're not worried

07:48.480 --> 07:49.914
About threatening
a murder victim?

07:51.683 --> 07:53.283
>> guys, I'm on the job.

07:56.120 --> 07:59.355
Check with occd.
Gonzo ruiz.

07:59.422 --> 08:02.056
>> all right, you just give me
a shove then.

08:02.124 --> 08:03.557
>> I'm outta here.

08:03.625 --> 08:05.659
>> hey, hey, hey, hey,
sit down.

08:05.727 --> 08:09.362
All right.
Let's talk about rick siebert.

08:09.430 --> 08:10.597
>> I bought siebert's debt.

08:10.665 --> 08:12.434
They put me
into play in his neighborhood.

08:12.501 --> 08:14.135
>> you wouldn't buy a debt
knowing it was bad.

08:14.203 --> 08:15.570
That'd make you look stupid.

08:15.638 --> 08:17.638
>> he's a dumb kid from jersey
hooked on drugs.

08:17.706 --> 08:19.140
Always scheming his way
on the street,

08:19.208 --> 08:20.674
And people fronted him
'cause he said

08:20.742 --> 08:22.208
Big family money was coming.

08:22.276 --> 08:24.343
>> from her family.

08:24.411 --> 08:25.511
>> everybody knew
who she was.

08:25.579 --> 08:27.412
And siebert said
her family owed them.

08:27.480 --> 08:29.981
Whatever that means.

08:33.318 --> 08:35.287
>> turns out rick siebert had
a marketable skill.

08:35.355 --> 08:36.955
These files from his laptop

08:37.023 --> 08:40.291
Have hayes-fitzgerald's
personal e-mails.

08:40.359 --> 08:41.859
>> he hacked in.
What did he get?

08:41.486 --> 08:43.154
>> well, for one thing
correspondence

08:43.221 --> 08:45.122
Between the councilman
and his contractor

08:45.189 --> 08:46.389
That fed the tabloids.

08:46.457 --> 08:48.490
Could be the family money
he was talking about.

08:48.557 --> 08:52.025
>> but the killing was
after he sold to the tabloids.

08:52.093 --> 08:55.094
>> revenge?

08:55.162 --> 09:00.098
>> or maybe he threatened
something bigger to come?

09:00.166 --> 09:01.566
>> rick siebert wasn't welcome
in our home.

09:01.634 --> 09:04.401
Unfortunately, that meant
we didn't see much of stacy.

09:04.469 --> 09:06.369
>> but you paid her rent.

09:06.437 --> 09:08.037
>> well, we knew he was gonna
sponge off of her.

09:08.105 --> 09:09.806
But it kept her
from sleeping in the street.

09:09.873 --> 09:11.941
>> even with rick siebert's
failings,

09:12.008 --> 09:13.108
He was a computer whiz.

09:13.176 --> 09:17.078
I mean, he hacked
into your e-mails.

09:17.146 --> 09:18.780
>> siebert sold that stuff
to the tabloids?

09:18.847 --> 09:21.115
>> he never made demands
on you?

09:21.183 --> 09:23.851
<i>For a bigger payday
than what he got at the ledger?</i>

09:23.918 --> 09:26.553
>> those stories are fabricated
from accounting errors.

09:26.621 --> 09:30.056
I would never have given him
anything anyway.

09:30.123 --> 09:32.091
>> he told people
he had more money coming.

09:32.159 --> 09:35.360
Maybe for material
of even greater value.

09:35.428 --> 09:36.828
>> he was
a delusional crackhead.

09:36.895 --> 09:38.029
Why would you listen
to him?

09:38.096 --> 09:40.497
>> and stacy?

09:40.565 --> 09:43.467
>> let's leave stacy
out of this.

09:43.534 --> 09:45.168
I don't think she had anything
to do with it.

09:45.236 --> 09:48.237
>> you honestly believe that?

09:49.906 --> 09:51.573
>> can you prove otherwise?

09:56.612 --> 09:58.746
I didn't think so.
Ahem.

09:58.813 --> 10:03.249
I have a meeting.

10:03.317 --> 10:05.817
>> very forgiving
toward his stepdaughter

10:05.885 --> 10:08.953
Who nearly got him knocked out
of a mayoral race.

10:09.021 --> 10:11.555
>> let's talk to the contractor
who stands to lose millions

10:11.623 --> 10:13.223
In city projects.

10:14.592 --> 10:17.026
>> I was at a bar, harley's,
having a beer,

10:17.094 --> 10:18.661
Watching the game
with some of my guys.

10:18.728 --> 10:20.596
>> who will back you up
to keep their jobs.

10:20.664 --> 10:22.231
>> who will tell the truth.

10:22.298 --> 10:23.532
Why would I want to kill
that punk?

10:23.600 --> 10:25.133
I didn't even know him.

10:25.201 --> 10:29.003
>> rick siebert, he smeared you
with some very inside dirt.

10:29.071 --> 10:30.805
>> sticks and stones,
detective.

10:30.873 --> 10:33.074
>> on the news, you said
you'd find the creep

10:33.142 --> 10:35.376
Who spread those lies
and deal with him.

10:35.444 --> 10:38.145
>> I was mad.
Maybe I meant it a few days ago.

10:38.213 --> 10:40.814
But providence stepped in.

10:40.882 --> 10:42.949
>> providence could have been
someone you hired.

10:43.017 --> 10:46.119
>> oh, please, I'm losing trade
from tabloid headlines.

10:46.186 --> 10:47.720
I'm gonna compound my problems?

10:47.788 --> 10:52.925
I'm gonna risk the whole
operation by hiring a hit?

10:52.993 --> 10:55.360
>> okay,
harley's till what time.

10:55.428 --> 11:00.699
>> last call.
I got business.

11:00.767 --> 11:01.700
>> mom, you don't need
to wait.

11:01.768 --> 11:03.001
I'll get a cab.

11:03.068 --> 11:04.469
>> you're not going back
to your place.

11:04.536 --> 11:05.470
It's too dangerous.

11:05.538 --> 11:07.038
>> like I'm going with you.

11:07.106 --> 11:08.973
I'm over 18.
I can go where I please.

11:09.041 --> 11:12.544
>> which is why you're here.
Thank god you're alive.

11:12.611 --> 11:14.345
>> I can get by on my own.

11:14.413 --> 11:17.415
>> based on recent events,
I think you need us

11:17.483 --> 11:19.250
More than we need you.

11:19.318 --> 11:21.552
Josie, did you tell her about
sophie's little hunger strike?

11:21.620 --> 11:23.086
>> what?

11:23.153 --> 11:25.152
>> she misses you, stacy.

11:25.219 --> 11:28.215
Both kids want you home.

11:28.283 --> 11:30.949
>> and they found crack
in that apartment.

11:31.017 --> 11:34.885
So you could face
drug possession charges.

11:34.953 --> 11:35.953
You're gonna need us.

11:38.123 --> 11:39.956
Just like you did before.

11:48.797 --> 11:49.634
Did you know Rick Siebert

11:49.657 --> 11:50.923
As an addict?

11:50.991 --> 11:52.424
Why didn't stacy live
with you?

11:52.492 --> 11:54.426
>> excuse me, addict or not,
the death of a young man

11:54.493 --> 11:56.460
And the wounding of our child
is a tragedy.

11:56.528 --> 11:58.362
>> he is slick.

11:58.430 --> 12:01.364
Hayes-fitzgerald
just tap-danced

12:01.432 --> 12:03.835
Very effectively to the tune
of siebert's death.

12:03.903 --> 12:05.539
>> must be in his genes.

12:05.607 --> 12:10.481
His great-grandfather was
a tammany ward heeler.

12:10.549 --> 12:13.117
And then he was made
building commissioner

12:13.184 --> 12:14.418
When his predecessor was found

12:14.485 --> 12:16.319
Floating
under the 59th street bridge.

12:16.387 --> 12:18.688
>> [sighs]

12:18.756 --> 12:21.557
Hayes-fitzgerald.
What's with the fancy hyphenate?

12:21.625 --> 12:24.426
>> hayes is his mom's side
of the family.

12:24.494 --> 12:26.528
Now they've run city hall
on three occasions.

12:26.596 --> 12:28.130
>> which might have given her

12:28.197 --> 12:29.464
Some useful connections.

12:29.532 --> 12:31.300
>> these are the files
that rick siebert hacked into.

12:31.367 --> 12:33.902
This all
from the councilman's e-mails?

12:33.970 --> 12:37.839
>> he has correspondence
on rare wines.

12:37.907 --> 12:41.308
>> a chat room for oenophiles.

12:41.375 --> 12:43.877
<i>Not worth a headline
in the ledger.</i>

12:43.944 --> 12:46.445
>> yeah, but the effort
that rick made

12:46.513 --> 12:51.215
To put all this stuff together,
put it all into files...

12:51.282 --> 12:54.184
You know, it's like he had
the scent of something

12:54.252 --> 12:59.355
He thought was real value.

12:59.423 --> 13:00.956
>> so, attacking
your stepfather's career,

13:01.024 --> 13:04.259
Was that rick's idea
or yours?

13:04.327 --> 13:07.395
>> he knows?
>> we've spoken about it.

13:07.463 --> 13:08.863
But he doesn't believe
you were involved.

13:08.931 --> 13:10.465
He's certain
it was all rick's idea.

13:10.533 --> 13:13.735
>> well, it was.
Just for money.

13:15.838 --> 13:20.238
>> stacy, you wrote
"screw the bastard"

13:20.305 --> 13:21.307
On the margin
of one of the articles

13:21.375 --> 13:23.910
About your stepdad.

13:23.978 --> 13:26.611
To me, that seems like anger.

13:29.014 --> 13:31.815
>> I'm home now.

13:31.883 --> 13:33.116
I won't talk about that.

13:33.184 --> 13:35.018
>> she shouldn't have to.

13:35.086 --> 13:38.188
Stacy,
like many young girls, went

13:38.256 --> 13:42.725
Through a rebellious phase,
but we're all back together now.

13:47.197 --> 13:49.198
>> let's talk
abt the shooter.

13:49.265 --> 13:52.033
Any facial hair?
Scars?

13:52.101 --> 13:53.667
Piercings?

13:53.735 --> 13:57.335
>> he had a hat on.
His sleeves were pushed up.

13:57.403 --> 14:02.241
On his wrists and arms,
he had tattoos.

14:02.308 --> 14:04.576
Snakes or barbed wire.

14:04.644 --> 14:09.280
>> do you think
he thought you were dead?

14:11.349 --> 14:12.716
>> I don't know.

14:12.784 --> 14:17.453
He just shot, looked us over,
and left.

14:19.989 --> 14:23.158
>> if the killers
were after drug debt,

14:23.225 --> 14:24.692
Would have killed 'em,
you know,

14:24.760 --> 14:26.694
See that they were packed
for aruba...

14:26.762 --> 14:29.931
>> and tear the place open
looking for drugs, money.

14:29.999 --> 14:33.234
>> leaving the girl,
it's not a pro's move

14:33.301 --> 14:36.169
Unless they had
specific instructions.

14:36.237 --> 14:38.037
I mean, that brings it
closer to home.

14:38.105 --> 14:40.739
>> we should file a court order
for camille's laptop.

14:40.807 --> 14:42.875
>> yeah, and the wine
correspondence thing,

14:42.942 --> 14:45.977
It sounds like, you know,
like old mob code.

14:46.044 --> 14:48.912
You know, like tony needs
a shirt and a half

14:48.979 --> 14:50.446
By mother's day,
blah, blah, blah.

14:50.514 --> 14:52.815
>> we'll check on
the councilman's true passion

14:52.882 --> 14:54.616
For the grape.

14:54.684 --> 14:57.551
>> the councilman leaves
most selections to me.

14:57.619 --> 15:01.754
Last month, I sent him
this saint julienne.

15:01.821 --> 15:05.189
Full-bodied.
Long, beautiful finish.

15:05.257 --> 15:08.858
>> yeah, the councilman,
he keeps going on and on

15:08.926 --> 15:13.295
About a chateau jeunesse
'94 cab, right?

15:13.363 --> 15:16.564
<i>>> but it's a boire
dans sa jeunesse.</i>

