with the cops,

16:50.586 --> 16:52.353
I have other people
who want that lease.

16:52.420 --> 16:59.192
>> take the over
on Thursday's game in philly.

16:59.260 --> 17:03.561
Forget about it.
You should know me by now.

17:03.629 --> 17:05.663
>> I never bet college baskets.

17:05.731 --> 17:07.397
That's a degenerate's game.

17:07.465 --> 17:10.000
>> mr. Di rogga.

17:10.068 --> 17:11.968
We're here 'cause we need
something moved.

17:12.036 --> 17:14.637
>> what?
>> this is a trucking company.

17:14.704 --> 17:17.973
>> everyone's out
on long hauls right now.

17:18.041 --> 17:19.876
>> well, we're here
on a short haul.

17:19.944 --> 17:23.614
You from here
to our headquarters.

17:23.682 --> 17:27.285
>> well, that would involve
my lawyer.

17:27.353 --> 17:29.621
>> you're quite a dedicated
fisherman, mr. Di rogga,

17:29.688 --> 17:32.156
Buying a boat midwinter.

17:32.224 --> 17:34.024
>> it's the right economy
to buy anything.

17:34.092 --> 17:37.361
>> and paying to dry-dock it
the rest of the winter?

17:40.865 --> 17:44.200
>> so where did you get
that 19,000 in cash from?

17:44.268 --> 17:46.369
>> it wasn't half that much.

17:46.437 --> 17:48.237
The guy was dying
to get rid of it.

17:48.305 --> 17:52.608
>> hmm, your new york
registration number.

17:52.676 --> 17:54.010
The seller, mr. Owens,

17:54.078 --> 17:56.779
Listed the purchase price
as $19,500.

17:56.847 --> 18:01.583
>> we'd really like to know
where that money came from.

18:04.071 --> 18:07.038
>> it was a token
of appreciation.

18:05.786 --> 18:09.021
I have a small trucking business
that hauls antiques

18:09.089 --> 18:10.556
For wealthy clients.

18:10.624 --> 18:12.525
They appreciate the care
I take.

18:12.593 --> 18:14.627
>> and they give you wads
of cash?

18:14.694 --> 18:15.728
>> oh, don't worry.

18:15.795 --> 18:20.832
Come tax time,
I'll report it.

18:20.900 --> 18:25.035
>> can I see your hand?

18:25.102 --> 18:27.703
>> sure.

18:27.771 --> 18:32.307
See something you like, I'll set
you up with my manicurist.

18:32.375 --> 18:35.543
>> well, you know,
our divers recovered

18:35.611 --> 18:38.647
This walther ppk .380

18:38.714 --> 18:40.314
From the river.

18:40.382 --> 18:42.582
Specifically from the port

18:42.649 --> 18:45.315
Where your van was spotted
making an illegal entry.

18:45.383 --> 18:48.950
You know, the funny thing is
about a walther ppk

18:49.018 --> 18:54.187
Is that it has a short grip.

18:54.254 --> 18:55.554
You know, see,

18:55.622 --> 19:00.590
When you load the clip,
you can pinch your little finger

19:00.657 --> 19:03.725
Very similar
to the pinch that you have.

19:03.793 --> 19:08.062
>> you have nothing tying
that gun to my client.

19:08.129 --> 19:10.097
We've been very cooperative.

19:10.164 --> 19:11.264
But I think
we're finished here.

19:11.332 --> 19:12.565
>> one more thing.

19:12.633 --> 19:14.133
Can you pull up your sleeves?

19:20.573 --> 19:23.041
>> looking
for something special?

19:23.108 --> 19:26.077
>> we're done, johnny.

19:32.115 --> 19:34.549
>> very smart.
Used a temporary tattoo.

19:34.617 --> 19:36.283
Deliberately kept
his sleeves up

19:36.351 --> 19:39.819
To draw attention
away from his face.

19:39.710 --> 19:42.710
The girl is key to
keeping a lid on things.

19:43.791 --> 19:46.391
Stacy's here.
What's your concern?

19:46.662 --> 19:49.862
She's fragile. She needs
an anchor to windward.

19:50.193 --> 19:54.093
There's only one person who
knows how to do that, who can do that.

19:59.247 --> 20:01.581
>> are you coming up now,
honey?

20:01.649 --> 20:04.650
>> did you take your pill?
>> mm-hmm.

20:04.718 --> 20:07.786
>> I'll be up
in a minute.

20:13.091 --> 20:14.524
Don't even say it.

20:14.592 --> 20:16.226
>> I can't help it.

20:16.294 --> 20:18.295
Why you picked her.

20:18.362 --> 20:21.530
Why not the girl
from the upstate family?

20:21.598 --> 20:23.565
Money, serious clout in albany.

20:23.633 --> 20:24.799
>> enough, ma.

20:24.867 --> 20:29.171
Josie has been very...

20:29.239 --> 20:30.608
Accepting.

20:33.046 --> 20:37.750
>> [laughs]

20:43.678 --> 20:43.845
[knock at door]

20:43.892 --> 20:44.793
>> stacy, honey?

20:45.740 --> 20:47.941
>> just a minute.

20:51.031 --> 20:52.567
>> you shouldn't be in here
all alone.

20:53.635 --> 20:54.735
You're on medication.

20:54.802 --> 20:57.304
>> then I'll get out.

21:01.676 --> 21:03.477
I need that towel.

21:12.620 --> 21:15.622
>> [sighs]

21:21.196 --> 21:22.963
Remember how you liked that?

21:23.030 --> 21:24.364
>> please don't.

21:30.036 --> 21:31.836
>> you'll always be my girl.

21:31.904 --> 21:36.541
You'll always be my girl.

22:07.168 --> 22:09.035
>> type and cross.
Prepare for intubation.

22:09.103 --> 22:10.770
Breathe her.
>> I got a bp. 70 palp.

22:10.838 --> 22:14.007
>> please, you got to save her.
Please.

22:19.626 --> 22:21.293
>> dr. Lansing,
our attending psychiatrist,

22:21.360 --> 22:23.161
Wants to stop by
when you feel you're ready.

22:23.229 --> 22:25.530
>> he needn't bother.

22:25.597 --> 22:28.432
>> you're on suicide watch
until he approves your release.

22:28.500 --> 22:30.567
>> I'm in no hurry to leave.

22:37.974 --> 22:40.542
>> the information
you gave us about rick,

22:40.610 --> 22:42.544
It was very helpful.

22:42.611 --> 22:44.512
>> I'm glad someone was helped.

22:48.083 --> 22:49.850
>> I was wondering
if you're feeling well enough

22:49.917 --> 22:52.852
To look at some photos.

22:54.855 --> 22:56.589
Just, if you see the man
that you described,

22:56.656 --> 22:59.258
Just tell me, okay?

22:59.325 --> 23:01.459
>> do we know
why he shot rick?

23:01.527 --> 23:03.161
>> no, we don't know that yet.

23:07.532 --> 23:13.303
[beeping]

23:20.610 --> 23:22.143
We just need
a few more minutes.

23:22.211 --> 23:23.310
>> she needs her rest.

23:23.378 --> 23:27.113
>> maybe you could just go
back over there.

23:27.181 --> 23:29.515
>> I'm fine.

23:43.163 --> 23:45.531
Actually, I don't think
I'm ready

23:45.598 --> 23:47.232
To do something
like this.

23:47.300 --> 23:50.369
>> it's okay.

23:53.006 --> 23:55.774
You've been through a lot.

23:55.842 --> 23:57.209
I understand.

24:03.483 --> 24:09.054
It must have been tough being
in that situation back at home.

24:09.122 --> 24:10.355
>> you don't know anything
about that.

24:10.423 --> 24:11.856
>> that's not true.

24:11.424 --> 24:14.126
I came from a bad home.

24:14.193 --> 24:16.862
You said,

24:16.929 --> 24:22.367
When bad things are happening,
you need to...

24:22.434 --> 24:24.669
Take yourself away
to another place.

24:24.737 --> 24:27.172
That's what I used to do.

24:27.239 --> 24:28.673
I used to just want
to lift myself up

24:28.741 --> 24:30.976
And take myself
to another place.

24:31.043 --> 24:34.112
You know, so I could see things
from somewhere else.

24:37.516 --> 24:42.153
>> maybe it was just the crack.

24:42.221 --> 24:44.289
>> I think we both know
that that's not true.

24:47.192 --> 24:49.994
>> I know
what you're thinking.

24:50.062 --> 24:52.063
You're wrong.

25:01.806 --> 25:04.474
>> my life has been
about saving stacy from herself.

25:04.542 --> 25:06.476
I homeschooled her
in the 9th grade.

25:06.544 --> 25:08.278
>> well, that can't have been
easy with your new baby.

25:08.345 --> 25:09.513
>> we had good help.

25:09.581 --> 25:10.948
We were all in europe
that year.

25:11.016 --> 25:13.250
>> come here, sophie.
Let mommy tie your shoe.

25:13.318 --> 25:14.451
>> and they had me.

25:14.519 --> 25:16.219
I have friends who stayed
in their villa.

25:16.287 --> 25:18.323
It was magnificent.

25:18.391 --> 25:20.025
Is that detective
still in there with her?

25:20.092 --> 25:21.092
>> yes.

25:21.160 --> 25:22.227
>> you can't hold stacy
to anything

25:22.295 --> 25:23.595
She says
after what she's been through.

25:23.663 --> 25:28.233
But she'll be home,
part of our family again.

25:28.300 --> 25:30.969
Like our time in siena.

25:31.037 --> 25:33.138
That was real happiness.

25:35.207 --> 25:36.374
>> they moved to europe.

25:36.442 --> 25:39.377
Odd choice for a politician
with a hot career.

25:39.445 --> 25:40.979
>> you know, we subpoenaed
stacy's records

25:41.046 --> 25:43.414
From dalecrest high.

25:43.482 --> 25:47.318
And she'd been acting out.
They recommended therapy.

25:47.386 --> 25:51.589
But instead her parents pulled
her out for homeschooling.

25:51.656 --> 25:53.424
>> well,
some people view therapy

25:53.491 --> 25:56.460
As an indictment
of their parenting skills.

25:56.527 --> 26:00.197
>> bigger reason
to duck out of therapy:

26:00.264 --> 26:03.199
Sexual abuse
by her stepfather.

26:05.803 --> 26:06.903
>> that's a headline
to die for

26:06.970 --> 26:08.271
If siebert knew about it.

26:08.338 --> 26:11.740
>> yeah, we don't have
direct evidence,

26:11.808 --> 26:15.877
But, you know, I think
he might have been onto it.

26:15.945 --> 26:18.179
>> hayes-fitzgerald's wife
could have known.

26:18.280 --> 26:20.380
> Well we've seen this before.

26:20.381 --> 26:24.981
After the initial outrage fear of
the shame overcomes everything.

26:24.982 --> 26:26.882
The wife joins with
the husband to keep it in-house.

26:26.883 --> 26:29.483
Even more of an
imperative in a political family.

26:29.597 --> 26:30.530
>> and camille?

26:30.598 --> 26:32.432
>> anything on the laptop?

26:32.500 --> 26:33.734
>> some cryptic e-mails.

26:33.801 --> 26:37.070
She refers to a potentially
volatile situation.

26:37.138 --> 26:38.905
>> use it.

26:38.973 --> 26:44.110
Find the raw nerve that breaks
through the family wall.

26:44.178 --> 26:47.180
>> so has the inconvenience
caused me by taking my laptop

26:47.248 --> 26:48.548
Been of some value?

26:48.616 --> 26:51.885
>> we're curious
about this volatile situation

26:51.952 --> 26:53.386
You've mentioned
in your e-mails to neil.

26:53.454 --> 26:58.258
>> volatile situations are
a daily occurrence in politics.

26:58.325 --> 26:59.626
>> well, I'll bring you closer
to home.

26:59.693 --> 27:04.030
You raised money for
the hayes-fitzgerald library,

27:04.098 --> 27:06.666
The beautification
of van-cortlandt park,

27:06.734 --> 27:10.303
And st. Lioba's, a shelter
for runaway teens.

27:10.371 --> 27:12.004
The strange thing
about that,

27:12.072 --> 27:14.540
This shelter got three times
what the others got.

27:14.608 --> 27:17.577
>> why should
my personal charities be

27:17.644 --> 27:19.645
Of any concern to you?

27:19.713 --> 27:20.746
>> well, these other
fundraisers,

27:20.814 --> 27:23.482
They're longstanding projects.

27:23.550 --> 27:25.218
But your interest
in st. Lioba's

27:25.285 --> 27:26.986
Surfaced just a few years ago.

27:27.054 --> 27:30.156
>> shortly after stacy left
dalecrest high.

27:30.223 --> 27:34.059
>> investigating an addict's
death does not give you

27:34.127 --> 27:36.528
The right to question
my personal generosity.

27:36.596 --> 27:39.398
I've had enough.

27:39.466 --> 27:41.433
I'm calling the commissioner.

27:44.771 --> 27:47.740
>> it's a raw nerve, huh?

27:52.078 --> 27:55.380
>> [sighs]
they have nothing.

27:55.448 --> 27:58.450
But they're fishing.
I'm worried.

27:58.517 --> 27:59.851
We don't want them
in stacy's records.

27:59.919 --> 28:04.122
I'm gonna call
the shelter director.

28:04.189 --> 28:06.324
>> if I had taken one
of these lucrative positions

28:06.392 --> 28:07.959
I was offered
in the private sector,

28:08.027 --> 28:11.162
I'd be immune
to this grief.

28:11.230 --> 28:14.198
>> that's not who you are.

28:14.266 --> 28:16.901
That is not who we are.

28:16.969 --> 28:19.871
The powerful in city governments
are a dying breed.

28:19.938 --> 28:23.941
The dalys in chicago,
a handful of others.

28:24.009 --> 28:26.711
This is our time, son.

28:26.778 --> 28:32.216
In an age of weakness,
you have a chance at real power.

28:38.123 --> 28:39.757
>> stacy is coming home,
everybody.

28:39.825 --> 28:41.258
>> that's great.

28:41.326 --> 28:42.560
The kids really miss you.

28:42.627 --> 28:45.596
>> sophie, tell your sister
how you feel

28:45.664 --> 28:46.764
When she's not around.

28:46.832 --> 28:49.300
>> sad. You wanna come home,
don't you?

28:49.367 --> 28:51.902
>> it's not that.

28:51.970 --> 28:53.904
You know I love you,
cutie.

28:57.676 --> 28:59.910
>> oh, back again?

28:59.978 --> 29:02.880
This is becoming harassment.

29:02.947 --> 29:05.582
>> we're looking for the man
who shot stacy.

29:05.650 --> 29:07.951
Why would that be
a problem?

29:08.019 --> 29:11.021
>> I just don't want
her pressured.

29:11.089 --> 29:12.890
Come on, kids.
Let's go.

29:12.957 --> 29:14.458
[grunts]

29:14.526 --> 29:17.327
We'll be in the hall.

29:17.395 --> 29:22.366
>> bye, stacy.

29:22.433 --> 29:24.101
Excuse me.

29:33.978 --> 29:36.779
>> I just saw him...

29:38.148 --> 29:39.716
You don't want him touching you?

29:44.121 --> 29:49.258
Stacy, it's hard
for victims

29:49.326 --> 29:52.895
Of this sort of thing
to have a normal relationship.

29:55.799 --> 29:59.101
Rick siebert...

29:59.169 --> 30:04.106
Might have caught on
to what was...

30:04.174 --> 30:05.908
>> yeah.

30:07.644 --> 30:09.812
>> he knew what happened.

30:12.282 --> 30:14.283
>> not at first.

30:17.654 --> 30:21.924
He asked me a lot of stuff.

30:21.992 --> 30:24.793
Like...

30:24.861 --> 30:27.363
Why I ran away and...

30:27.430 --> 30:29.264
What the shelter was like.

30:29.332 --> 30:32.134
>> st. Lioba's.

30:32.202 --> 30:35.671
>> rick might have threatened
blackmail

30:35.738 --> 30:39.207
Far beyond any kind
of political scandal.

30:39.275 --> 30:42.144
Which could have meant jail time
for your stepdad.

30:44.180 --> 30:46.515
>> and that's
why rick was killed.

30:54.824 --> 30:57.192
>> down here, jessica.

30:57.260 --> 30:58.960
So how should I make you feel
at home?

30:59.028 --> 31:01.162
>> this is like
your own private club.

31:01.230 --> 31:05.633
>> yeah, where I relax, enjoy
the pleasures of fine wine.

31:05.701 --> 31:08.436
I have a calvados
that once belonged to napoleon.

31:08.504 --> 31:11.205
>> so it's from
like 100 years ago?

31:11.273 --> 31:13.741
>> more like 200.

31:13.809 --> 31:14.909
>> can you still drink it?

31:14.977 --> 31:16.210
>> absolutely.

31:18.280 --> 31:20.048
Ah, you're cold.

31:20.116 --> 31:24.452
I have to keep it chilly in here
to protect the wine.

31:25.855 --> 31:27.289
Here.
Let me do you up.

31:34.898 --> 31:38.033
>> thanks for the tour.
I really appreciate your time.

31:38.101 --> 31:39.235
I know how busy you are.

31:39.303 --> 31:40.470
How about I talk to some people

31:40.537 --> 31:43.840
At city hall about
a summer internship program?

31:43.908 --> 31:45.508
>> that'd be awesome.
>> [laughs]

31:47.178 --> 31:49.446
>> daddy, daddy.
>> ah, who's my girl?

31:49.513 --> 31:53.450
>> me.
>> my girl and no one else's.

31:53.517 --> 31:56.619
Forever and ever.
>> ever and ever.

31:56.687 --> 31:57.954
>> [laughs]

32:09.065 --> 32:13.765
She's taken off from the house?
 We don't need that right now.

32:13.806 --> 32:14.806
 Ma, it'll be fine.

32:15.787 --> 32:17.387
That girl is unstable.

32:17.337 --> 32:19.837
So she's prowling the
 streets looking to get high. 

32:19.878 --> 32:24.578
Or talking to the cops. So
 much for keeping her grounded. 

32:24.619 --> 32:26.819
Hey I was supportive, even loving.

32:25.620 --> 32:30.320
And you went too far. 
You're always being led around by your.

32:30.361 --> 32:31.361
 Why do you
 always assume that I..

32:31.362 --> 32:32.362
 Because I know you.

32:40.723 --> 32:42.623
When I saw 
she'd gone I had to call you

32:48.434 --> 32:50.134
 guess we'll just play games.

32:52.435 --> 32:55.735
There's a reason why she doesn't
 want to share a roof with your husband.

32:58.269 --> 33:01.170
I think we all know
what that is.

33:04.707 --> 33:06.775
>> stacy says things,

33:06.842 --> 33:08.243
But she's not always telling
the truth.

33:08.310 --> 33:09.977
>> at what point
do you stop lying?

33:10.045 --> 33:12.145
How did he do it?

33:12.213 --> 33:14.015
Diminish you?

33:14.083 --> 33:17.919
Make you feel unworthy
of a man of his stature?

33:20.054 --> 33:23.056
How does someone justify
what he did?

33:25.694 --> 33:29.529
>> oh, god.

33:29.597 --> 33:32.331
>> how did you justify it?

33:34.934 --> 33:39.003
>> when the two of you met,
she was around 12.

33:41.373 --> 33:43.873
I've seen photos of her.
She was a beautiful girl.

33:43.941 --> 33:47.376
Did you consciously use that?

33:47.443 --> 33:50.712
>> no. My god, no.

33:50.779 --> 33:54.448
It--it just happened.

33:54.516 --> 33:56.550
>> and it happened again
and again and again.

33:56.617 --> 33:58.118
>> he loved me.

33:58.185 --> 34:00.353
>> and you paid for that
with access to your daughter.

34:02.356 --> 34:05.191
>> it's not just me.

